Sincere gratitude to everyone who joined us in Miami on Friday for the inaugural @whatsnextcon Art Basel. Over 700 of you registered for this premier experience that connects global business executives, influencers, and visionaries who truly move the world forward and sit at the intersection of innovation and culture. We had panels around art, tech, web3, venture capital and entertainment led by the people who make it happen. Why? Because we ought to connect, fellowship, build, inspire the next generation, and make deals. And what is an experience rooted in culture without an epicurean experience or music? It’s not complete to me…so thank you celebrity chef and restaurateur @amarisjones for blowing us away with the incredible brunch you curated and thank you to Grammy Award winning DJ @walshyfire for setting the tone and creating pure vibes. We had a time! Immense gratitude to our presenting partner @siliconvalleybank and their Access to Innovation team that continues to truly do the work. It’s an honor. Kudos to my amazing team that always makes everything look effortless. 🙌🏾 Follow @whatsnextcon to see…well “What’s Next!”

Last night for Machel Montano’s 40th year in entertainment anniversary concert!! Easily 20k+ people. I first became of fan of Machel Mantano when I was 11 years old. Anyone remember “Come Dig It”. He’s made the soundtrack of my Soca Life! My favorite song is “Water Flowing”
by Xtatik and Machel Montano. I recall 3 occasions when he performed the song live…twice in Trinidad and then Brooklyn Carnival with the Sesame Flyer mas camp and I promise you it literally starting raining and then stopped when they were done. 🤯 Yes we happily danced in the rain!! That was more than 15 years ago @kwedd51 is my witness for all 3 times. As his song “Never Again” says…”Well Done”. I’m excited to announce the launch of my new podcast “What’s Next with Umindi Francis” which will be live tomorrow on all major podcast platforms.
@whatsnextwithumindi 

This podcast explores perspectives from executives, creatives, and thought leaders at the intersection of business and strategy in fashion, beauty, tech, entertainment, web3 and more. The first Monday in May is the fashion industry’s biggest night. This year The Metropolitan Museum of Art’s Costume Institute pays homage to the late Karl Lagerfeld whose fashion career spanned more than six decades and included iconic Creative Director roles at Chanel, Fendi, and his eponymous brand Karl Lagerfeld.

What’s Next Podcast with Umindi Francis sits in conversation with Marjorie Hernandez @m_h_d_v co-founder of THE DEMETERIALISED and LUKSO (an Ethererum based blockchain for the new creative economy), to discuss her meteoric rise and her experience launching the first Karl Lagerfeld web3 experience on @thedemeterialsed her ground breaking digital fashion platform. 

Visit our YouTube platform to view the conversation discussing how this ground breaking web3 project came to be. 

Listen to the entire podcast on all leading podcast platforms including @spotifypodcasts @applepodcasts @googlepodcasts Class is in session!! 📝 🎙️

For many consumers there is a disconnect and confusion around web3. Major shifts in the market over the last year have only served to exacerbate the situation. What will it take for wide spread consumer adoption of web3 today? Marjorie Hernandez founder of @thedematerialised the first fashion digital asset market place and co-founder of @lukso an ethereum based blockchain, shares her insights on What’s Next Podcast with Umindi Francis @whatsnextwithumindi. Available @spotifypodcasts @applepodcasts @googlepodcasts and more…

WHAT’S NEXT WITH CARLY CUSHNIE 

@carlycushnie is a New York-based Creative Director and Fashion Designer who successfully ran her eponymous fashion brand for more than a decade. Her award winning highly coveted collection of elegant womenswear and its identifiable silhouettes, has left its mark on American Fashion. Regularly worn by A-list celebrities, and a staple on the red carpet, the collection has also retailed at some of the world’s leading stores. Today she continues to inform everything she touches—from the runway to lifestyle and home—with a refined yet eclectic style, Cushnie has established herself as an innovative force in the fashion and design world with projects ranging from her collection at Target to designing for the American Ballet Theatre and interior design. 

This week on What’s Next Podcast with Umindi Francis Carly shares her journey, insights on the industry,
and of course…what’s next! 

Tune in on all leading audio platforms for more…🎙️
@spotifypodcasts @spotifyforpodcasters @applepodcasts @googlepodcasts ….

Ade Samuel @adesamuel is a native New Yorker and world-renowned fashion stylist. Ade has worked with some of the most famous names in Hollywood such as Michael B. Jordan, Christina Aguilera, Daniel Kaluuya, Letitia Wright, Miley Cyrus, Khaled, Cynthia Erivo, Big Sean, Nicole Richie, Yara Shahidi, Rosie-Huntington Whitely, Naomie Harris and the City Girls to name a few. She has been profiled in the New York Times and Wall Street Journal and often appears on @goodmorningamerica She is the recipient of the prestigious @harlemsfashionrow Stylist of the Year Award in 2022. Her mission is to bridge the gap between American and Nigerian fashion, using her creative approach to cutting-edge style.
 
We talk about her journey to becoming a fashion stylist, her collection at Macy’s, how she’s conquered social media, and what she has in store as a creative director.

This is What’s Next Podcast with Umindi Francis. Let’s Go!

social_posts.post_text:
The WIE Suite takes Cannes Lions.
It’s an honor to be a member of this powerful network of women in C-Suite positions globally. During Cannes Lions @deepoku Founder & CEO of the @thewiesuite organized the fourth annual Cannes Lions "A Dinner For Women", celebrating business leaders and culture creators. As Dee said, “What a powerful crew of trailblazing women, from the likes of McKinsey, Hearst, EY, Tik Tok, Pinterest, Google, New York Stock Exchange, RGA, Blavity, WPP, UGG, Edelman, Nasdaq, Wieden Kennedy, Vice, Meta, Spotify, Maximum Effort, Hello Sunshine, Time Magazine and more.” 
 
We had an incredible time at dinner but we also supported each other the entire week. We connected, collaborated, had fun and were inspired to continue building towards a more equitable future together. Because when women win…everyone wins!!
 
We also enjoyed a lovely fireside chat with @kenyahunt Editor in Chief of Elle UK who talked about utilizing the networks we have rather than waiting around for bigger sustainable change, and how reverse mentorship by the young women she supports has actually contributed to her own self care. 

Thank you @deepoku for your selfless work and constantly doing your all to uplift us all. It is appreciated and you my dear are unstoppable…and so are all the women of The Wie Suite. 

Swipe to see how completely giddy we were to see each other ❤️

Maria Brito @mariabrito_ny is an award-winning contemporary art advisor, entrepreneur, author, and curator. Her latest bestselling book, “How Creativity Rules The World,” was a winner of the International Book Awards in the Business and Entrepreneurship Categories, as well as chosen by Next Big Idea Club as one of the best business and creativity books of 2022.
 
She has worked with some of the world’s most renowned artists and institutions and has been an art advisor for many notable celebrities. In 2020, Brito was named by Art News as one of the visionaries who have shaped the art world, and Complex Magazine selected her as one of the 20 power players in the world of art.
 
In this episode, we discuss her groundbreaking work as an art advisor, the economics of art consultancy, boosting creativity for entrepreneurs, her superpowers as a marketer, her recent Tedx talk, and her big pivot. After studying at Harvard, Maria became a corporate attorney and then made a switch!

This is Season 2 with What’s Next Podcast with Umindi Francis. Let’s go!
